Package nl.naturalis.geneious.csv

Class CsvImportConfig<T extends Enum<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.naturalis.geneious.csv.CsvImportConfig<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BoldImportConfig, CrsImportConfig, SampleSheetImportConfig
    public abstract class CsvImportConfig<T extends Enum<T>>
extends Object
    Contains the user input driving the import of CSV-like files (BOLD Import, CRS Import, Sample Sheet Import). Subclasses may specify additionally required user input (e.g. the sample sheet importer needs to know whether or not to create dummies), but they all need to know things like the field delimiter.
    Author:
    Ayco Holleman

      • getColumnNumbers

        public abstract nl.naturalis.common.collection.EnumToIntMap<T> getColumnNumbers()
        Returns a mapping of symbolic column names to actual column numbers. We use symbolic column names (e.g. see BoldColumn) rather than column numbers to make the code less error prone. All subclasses of CsvImportConfig currently return a hard-coded map. However in the future, we might need user input to properly configure a column mapping or to make it less rigid.
        Returns:
